Software is painfully slow (TV Plus bloat), setup is infuriating (mounting/stud issues, cable routing), and even Samsung‚Äôs S801D soundbar drops audio over Wi‚ÄëFi, forcing a lower‚Äëquality Bluetooth fallback. comments.comment_text_display:
to be clear the wifi connection isn't on 6, that's a backhaul/device comm channel, which is... normal-ish? for wifi 7 equipment when leadership/marketing drives instead of engineers. the... thinking... there is that since literally everything used in home construction (even non insulated interior walls with a half-inch sheet of drywall on either side) blocks 6ghz at consumer broadcast strengths the interference inside of a room will be pretty limited

there are a lot of real world problems with this series of assumptions but it's not quite insanity. it's really easy to get pretty quiet on 6ghz even in an apartment building.

comments.comment_text_display: Why would 6ghz be worse for RF interference? Is there something else using that range in the USA or something? Here in the UK it's much easier to find clear channels in 6ghz. Majority of people will use the ISP supplied router which wont be Wi-Fi 6e or 7 capable. We recently tested 6ghz in a large city and we couldn't see any other 6ghz radios except our own broadcasting.
